div.div:
Implement __init__, load your h5 file, load your metadata dataframe,
implement a function called get indices, which retrieves the metadata table indices for an mlset. Eg: if mlset=training, retrieve the indices of the rows in the dataframe where mlset=training.
Store these indices in self.indices.
Implement __get_item__ function which takes in idx (not indices but different). This idx tells you which index to select, get the final index of image by self.indices[idx].
Using the above, load the image and the label from the h5 file and metadata table.
Make sure both the image and the label are numeric and are tensors or numpy arrays
Apply any monai augmentations if needed.
Return image, labels.

Pytorch lightning module class,

inherits from a monai model and pytorch lightning module.
__init__ function
should contain the model parameters, like learning rate, what dataset/dataloader you are using and any metric you want to compute.
It should also initialize the model itself.
Other functions:
Refer to lightning documentation
